<paragraph id="8628475BFFBB8508FF13FE88FCD7FE44" blockId="28.[136,1451,337,472]" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FF13FE88FEE9FE0C" bold="true" box="[189,294,374,400]" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species is recognized by the purple veined and mottled flowers with a suborbicular synsepal and purple lip with white fimbriate margins. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FDFFFE64FC9EFE28" authorityName="Kolanowska &amp; Szlachetko" authorityYear="2014" box="[593,849,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ortizianus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FDFFFE64FC9EFE28" box="[593,849,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">Myoxanthus ortizianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBB8508FC27FE65FBCBFE28" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[905,1028,411,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="priapus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBB8508FC27FE65FBCBFE28" box="[905,1028,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="239">M. priapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the only other species that have a suborbicular synsepal but not a lip with fimbriate margins.
</paragraph>
